						               													<description>From the Invisible City Productions website:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Multiply and spread in this strategic territory-claiming, piece-elimination game with a strong dose of chance for two to six organisms.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You Need&amp;#10;&amp;#10;* A Chinese checkers set.&amp;#10;    * Two 6-sided dice.&amp;#10;    * A capture cup for each player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, roll the dice, transform your pieces (either add or remove pieces on the board), then check for captures (based on the number of adjacent friendly and opposing pieces -- captured pieces, whether friendly or not, go to your capture cup).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when one player has no pieces left in play or in hand, or if there are no pieces on the board and all players have taken a turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have the most pieces in your capture cup at the end of the game, you win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
